ownedComment.body: AbstractTunnel is a so-called "mixin" class, i. e. during the mapping to GML its properties and associations are just copied to its subclasses (Tunnel and TunnelPart). This mechanism allows the handling of multiple inheritance, which is not supported by some platforms like XML. Hence, Tunnel is mapped to GML in a way that AbstractToplevelCityObject is its real superclass and AbstractCityObject is the real superclass of TunnelPart.
